      <section>
        <title>Italy: Mortgage vs Leasing</title>
        <chapter>
          <title>Mortgage - How does it work</title>
          <subtitle>In the last year mortgages increased + 97% in Italy.</subtitle>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>The bank accept to give a mortgage</item>
              <item>The customer receives the full amount of money from the bank to buy a property</item>
              <item>The customer buys the property and becomes immediately its owner</item>
              <item>The customer can return loan with rates for a maximum of 30 years</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>Features</title>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>Low tax 1.5% / 2.5%</item>
              <item>Settlement balance in advance</item>
              <item>Banks are allowed to distrain the property after 18 unpaid rates</item>
              <item>Does not permit the possession of the property with a liquid under 80% property value</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>Leasing - How does it work</title>
          <subtitle>From January 2016 the lease was extended not only to industry but also to individuals for the purchase of properties, so leasingbecame an alternative to mortgages</subtitle>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>The bank accept to give a leasing</item>
              <item>The bank buys a property on real estate market,(so the bank has the ownership)</item>
              <item>The customer pays the full amount of the property to the bank with rates for a maximum of 20 years</item>
              <item>the change of ownership comes with the last ransom money</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
        <chapter>
          <title>Features</title>
          <paragraph>
            <list type="unordered">
              <item>High tax</item>
              <item>Settlement balance only after the last payment of rates</item>
              <item>Banks are allowed to distrain the property after 1 unpaid rate</item>
              <item>Permit the possession of the property with a slow liquid, 10% property value</item>
            </list>
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
